# StepFlow

This component is not yet externalized under Web Shell and therefore should not be used outside of local development. Until further notice, please use the [QBDS version](https://uxfabric.intuitcdn.net/internal/design-systems/qbds/main/latest/index.html?path=/story/components-stepflowhorizontal--playground&theme=quickbooks&colorScheme=light) of this component.

The StepFlow has two primary patterns:

- To help users complete a complicated task or a series of tasks or decisions that affect other choices they’ll need to make later. Connecting a bank account and other setup flows are good examples.
- To help users fill out a long form by breaking it into several small sections. Good examples are creating a new employee and signing up for payments.

## Installation & Import

```bash
yarn add @ids-ts/step-flow
```

```tsx
import { StepFlow } from '@ids-ts/step-flow';
```

## Props API

| Prop | Type | Required | Description |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| `activeStep` | `number` | No | [internal] The current step index |
| `activeStepIndex` | `number` | Yes | The step the flow begins on |
| `activeNestedStep` | `number` | No | [internal] The index of the active nested step, used in progress calculations |
| `children` | `React.ReactNode` | Yes | The steps to be displayed within the container |
| `className` | `string` | No | Custom classes to be added to the StepFlow div |
| `goToNext` | `() => void` | No | [internal] Advances stepIndex to the next step in the flow |
| `goToPrevious` | `() => void` | No | [internal] Advances stepIndex to the previous step in the flow |
| `goToStep` | `(stepIndex: number) => void` | No | [internal] Goes directly to the provided step in the flow |
| `navigationDirection` | `'forward' | 'backward'` | No | [internal] The direction to navigate to |
| `progressType` | `'indicator' | 'bar' | 'none'` | Yes | The type of progress bar. One of: “indicator”, “bar”, “none” |
| `setActiveNestedStep` | `Dispatcher<number>` | No | [internal] Setter for activeNestedStep |
| `width` | `Width` | Yes | The width of the containers in the flow steps. One of: “small”, “medium”, “large” |

<details>
<summary>Full TypeScript Interface</summary>

```typescript
export interface StepFlowProps extends ThemeableElement<'div'> {
  /** [internal] The current step index */
  activeStep?: number;
  /**  The step the flow begins on */
  activeStepIndex: number;
  /** [internal] The index of the active nested step, used in progress calculations */
  activeNestedStep?: number;
  /** The steps to be displayed within the container */
  children: React.ReactNode;
  /** Custom classes to be added to the StepFlow div */
  className?: string;
  /** [internal] Advances stepIndex to the next step in the flow */
  goToNext?: () => void;
  /** [internal] Advances stepIndex to the previous step in the flow */
  goToPrevious?: () => void;
  /** [internal] Goes directly to the provided step in the flow */
  goToStep?: (stepIndex: number) => void;
  /** [internal] The direction to navigate to */
  navigationDirection?: 'forward' | 'backward';
  /** The type of progress bar. One of: “indicator”, “bar”, “none” */
  progressType: 'indicator' | 'bar' | 'none';
  /** [internal] Setter for activeNestedStep */
  setActiveNestedStep?: Dispatcher<number>;
  /** The width of the containers in the flow steps. One of: “small”, “medium”, “large” */
  width: Width;
}

export type Width = 'small' | 'medium' | 'large';
```

</details>

